<div><div><h2>-</h2></div><div>uruguayan prosecutors are seeking to bring to trial at least <a href="https://www.yahoo.com/news/uruguay-accuses-5-suspects-links-mexican-drug-cartel-205602209.html">five individuals</a> detained on suspicion of laundering money for a powerful mexican drug cartel including at least one suspect allegedly linked to a company named in the panama papers. the five were among 11 initially detained in montevideo on friday by more than 30 law enforcement officials. the officials were already investigating but <a href="http://www.busqueda.com.uy/nota/la-policia-detuvo-en-uruguay-once-presuntos-vinculados-al-poderoso-cartel-de-la-droga-mexicano">decided to move quickly</a> to preempt any attempt at flight after the weekly online magazine busqueda reported that gerardo gonz\xc3\xa1lez valencia had used shell companies incorporated in panama to <a href="http://www.busqueda.com.uy/nota/un-estudio-uruguayo-obtuvo-traves-de-mossack-fonseca-sociedades-para-supuestos-narcos-mexicanos/ls-2333-249d9f7b776a25766476">buy real estate in uruguay</a> including a chalet in punta del este. the story was part of the panama papers investigation by icij german newspaper s\xc3\xbcddeutsche zeitung and more than 100 other news organizations that dug through 11.5 million files containing information on decades of operations by panama law firm and offshore company incorporator mossack fonseca and co. gonz\xc3\xa1lez valencia is linked to the rapidly expanding new generation cartel of jalisco (cjng) in mexico. his brother abigael gonz\xc3\xa1lez valencia now imprisoned in mexico headed the powerful \xe2\x80\x9clos cuinos\xe2\x80\x9d cartel. abigael gonz\xc3\xa1lez valencia has been designated a drug king pin in the united states along with his brother-in-law nemesis oseguera cervantes who leads cjng. the u.s. treasury department\xe2\x80\x99s office of foreign asset control said when it <a href="https://www.treasury.gov/press-center/press-releases/pages/jl10020.aspx">named the two kingpins</a> that the two organization \xe2\x80\x9chave rapidly expanded their criminal empire in recent years through the use of violence and corruption.\xe2\x80\x9d acting director of ofac john e. smith said then that they \xe2\x80\x9cnow rank among the most powerful drug trafficking organizations in mexico.\xe2\x80\x9d meanwhile icij partner the mcclatchy company news chain reported that ecuador\xe2\x80\x99s president rafael correa and his brother had been <a href="http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/national/article73448692.html">mentioned in a mossack fonseca email</a> to a law firm for which it provided shell corporations for its customers. sara montenegro a lawyer for mossack fonseca sent an email in may 2012 to a guayaquil firm \xe2\x80\x9cto notify you of an investigation being undertaken by the office of the anti-corruption prosecutor of panama in reference to misters fabricio correa and rafael correa delgado for the crime of embezzlement against the ecuadoran state an investigation which involves a panamanian corporation that was sold to you in 2006 called orlion group s.a.\xe2\x80\x9d the email was sent to a lawyer working for the legalsa &  asociados firm which had opened the offshore on behalf of an unidentified customer. the prosecutor wanted shareholder information \xe2\x80\x9cwhich we did not give since we don\xe2\x80\x99t have it\xe2\x80\x9d montenegro added. she asked legalsa &  asociados for information on the true owners of the orlion group s.a. because an official demand was likely. a few days later mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s head of compliance sandra de cornejo had recommended that her firm drop services to the orlion group s.a. \xe2\x80\x9calthough we have not found anything that ties the correas and the entity\xe2\x80\x9d she said \xe2\x80\x9ci suggest resigning \xe2\x80\xa6 because of the scant cooperation received from the client\xe2\x80\x9d which mossack fonseca had asked for \xe2\x80\x9cknow your customer\xe2\x80\x9d information two years before. mossack fonseca resigned as orlion group&#8217;s agent in july 2012. in an unrelated incident panamanian officials <a href="http://www.prensa.com/in_english/fiscalia-realiza-allanamiento-mossack-fonseca_21_4466763285.html">seized bags of shredded documents</a> during a search of one of the law firm\xe2\x80\x99s premises late last week. the search was conducted as part of an ongoing investigation into the law firm\xe2\x80\x99s activities. mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s panama city headquarters was <a href="/20160413-panama-raids-mossack-fonseca.html">raided by police</a> earlier in april. mossack fonseca said the shredded paperwork seized in the latest search were documents that had been digitized and were to be recycled. the firm said authorities had already obtained copies of these files during their initial search of the firm\xe2\x80\x99s headquarters.</div></div>